===Etymology===
French ''[[plastron]]'', from Italian ''[[piastrone]]'', augmentive of ''[[piastra]]'' ‘breastplate’, from Latin ''[[emplastrum]]'' ‘plaster’, from Greek [[εμπλαστρον]], from [[εμπλαστος]] ‘daubed, plastered’, from [[εμπλασσειν]] ‘to mould, form’.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/'plæstrən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The nearly flat part of the shell structure of a [[tortoise]] or other animal, similar in composition to the [[carapace]]
# {{fencing}} A [[half-jacket]] worn under the jacket for padding or for safety.

